definitions.output_implementation:
(meta, true_result, condition, false_result) ->
    if condition() then true_result() else false_result()

(meta, message) ->
    unless meta.memo.response
        meta.memo.response = prompt message()
    if meta.output_index is 0
        meta.memo.response

(meta, input) ->
    value = input()
    console.log value#    meta.runtime.log "runtime log #{window.JSON.stringify value}"
    value
(meta, text, pattern, replacement) -> text().replace pattern(), replacement()
(meta, message) -> confirm message()  if meta.output_index is 0

definitions.value: "Do you want to save the day?"

definitions.output_implementation:
(meta, obj, attribute, value) ->
    #console.log obj(), attribute(), value()
    obj = obj()
    obj[attribute()] = value()
    obj

(meta, obj, attribute) ->
    the_object = obj()
    delete the_object[attribute()]
    the_object
(meta, subroutine, inputs, output) -> subroutine().call(inputs(), output(), meta.runtime)

(meta, handler, delay) ->
    handler = handler()
    meta.runtime.setInterval handler, 0, delay()
    undefined
(meta, element, property, value) -> element().css property(), value() + "px"

(meta, object) ->
    pairs = []
    for key,value of object()
        pairs.push [key,value]
    pairs
